                <note rend="inline" type="source">325.1121 Bethune, Larry K./16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-30T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 30, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Department’s telegram 16, March 28, noon. Protection for Kaminsky, Ellis, and
                    Bethune of General Motors requested in friendly manner from Governor of Santiago
                    and willingly granted on March 20th, the day on which Kaminsky was assaulted.
                    Foreign Minister was also informed. Saturday night I thanked the Governor for
                    his action and indicated my continued interest in the protection which he had
                    accorded. He explained that a policeman had been assigned for the protection of
                    each of the three men menaced. Details of the assault have already been sent by
                    air mail. Local representatives of General Motors say this morning that they are
                    entirely satisfied with the protection granted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
